<subSubSection id="47A22ED7FF98FFE2FF24FB134853FA81" pageId="2" pageNumber="1573" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="0F077D5CFF98FFE2FF24FB134853FA81" blockId="2.[178,1086,1260,1311]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1573">Etymology: The specific epithet is an adjective derived from the Latin noun rastrum (hoe, hatchet) and aludes to the shape of the ventral process of the aedeagus.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="47A22ED7FF98FFE4FF24FAD04DF5FCA8" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="1575" pageId="2" pageNumber="1573" type="description">
<paragraph id="0F077D5CFF98FFE2FF24FAD04D39FAE1" blockId="2.[178,1085,1327,1407]" pageId="2" pageNumber="1573">
Description: Body length 
<quantity id="C840D0B9FF98FFE2FD8BFAD04ECAFADB" box="[541,663,1327,1349]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.05" metricValueMax="6.3" metricValueMin="5.8" pageId="2" pageNumber="1573" unit="mm" value="6.05" valueMax="6.3" valueMin="5.8">5.8-6.3 mm</quantity>
; length of forebody 
<quantity id="C840D0B9FF98FFE2FCFDFAD04FB8FADB" box="[875,997,1327,1349]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="3.8" metricValueMin="3.7" pageId="2" pageNumber="1573" unit="mm" value="3.75" valueMax="3.8" valueMin="3.7">3.7-3.8 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: body blackish; legs with dark-brown femora, brown tibiae, and dark-reddish tarsi; antennae reddish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F077D5CFF98FFE4FF24FA704CA7FE45" blockId="2.[178,1086,1423,1591]" lastBlockId="4.[178,1086,218,475]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="1575" pageId="2" pageNumber="1573">
Head (
<figureCitation id="978361D9FF98FFE2FF60FA704D6CFA3B" box="[246,305,1423,1445]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="3.[178,218,1516,1536]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1484]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1-8: Stilicoderus rastratus: (1) forebody; (2) median portion of head; (3) sutural portion of elytra; (4) posterior margin of male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6-7) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (8) apex of ventral process. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3, 5-7: 0.2 mm; 4, 8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303006/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1573">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) 1.10-1.15 times as long as broad and of oval shape; lateral margins behind eyes smoothly curving towards posterior constriction; posterior angles obsolete; punctation fine and sparse (
<figureCitation id="978361D9FF98FFE2FE1DFA364D96FA41" box="[395,459,1481,1503]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="3.[178,218,1516,1536]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1484]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1-8: Stilicoderus rastratus: (1) forebody; (2) median portion of head; (3) sutural portion of elytra; (4) posterior margin of male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6-7) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (8) apex of ventral process. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3, 5-7: 0.2 mm; 4, 8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303006/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="1573">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), only near posterior constriction with small area with larger and denser punctures; frons nearly impunctate; interstices distinctly broader than diameter of punctures, without distinct microsculpture. Eyes relatively small and weakly convex, approximately one third as long as postocular region from posterior margin of eye to posterior constriction. Antenna approximately 
<quantity id="C840D0B9FF9EFFE4FD4FFF254F7AFF6E" box="[729,807,218,240]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" unit="mm" value="1.7">1.7 mm</quantity>
long; antennomeres II and IV weakly oblong, III approximately 1.5 times as long as broad, V and VI approximately as broad as long, and VII-X weakly transverse. Labrum with smooth, oblong median elevation, on either side of this elevation with microsculptured oval impression, anterior margin of labrum concave, middle of this concavity with a pair of tooth-like projections. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="978361D9FF9EFFE4FEB0FE924D3EFE1D" box="[294,355,365,387]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="3.[178,218,1516,1536]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1484]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1-8: Stilicoderus rastratus: (1) forebody; (2) median portion of head; (3) sutural portion of elytra; (4) posterior margin of male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6-7) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (8) apex of ventral process. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3, 5-7: 0.2 mm; 4, 8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303006/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) approximately 1.1 times as long as broad and 0.9 times as broad as head; punctation fine and sparse, only posteriorly (near posterior margin and on either side of impunctate midline) denser and coarser; midline broadly impunctate; interstices glossy.
</paragraph>
<caption id="5BC72DD4FF99FFE3FF24FA13486EF9B3" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303006" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5303006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303006/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574" startId="3.[178,218,1516,1536]" targetBox="[178,1085,212,1484]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="0F077D5CFF99FFE3FF24FA13486EF9B3" blockId="3.[178,1086,1516,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF99FFE3FF24FA134D5FF99E" bold="true" box="[178,258,1516,1536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574">Figs 1-8</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF99FFE3FE86FA134D8AF99E" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[272,471,1516,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rastratus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF99FFE3FE86FA134D8AF99E" box="[272,471,1516,1536]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574">Stilicoderus rastratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: (
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF99FFE3FE7BFA134DA5F99E" bold="true" box="[493,504,1516,1536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574">1</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF99FFE3FDE7FA134E21F99E" bold="true" box="[625,636,1516,1536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574">2</emphasis>
) median portion of head; (
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF99FFE3FCE8FA134FD4F99E" bold="true" box="[894,905,1516,1536]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574">3</emphasis>
) sutural portion of elytra; (
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF99FFE3FF6FF9FD4D59F988" bold="true" box="[249,260,1538,1558]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574">4</emphasis>
) posterior margin of male sternite VII; (
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF99FFE3FDE2F9FD4E22F988" bold="true" box="[628,639,1538,1558]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574">5</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII; (
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF99FFE3FCD4F9FD4F3DF988" bold="true" box="[834,864,1538,1558]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574">6-7</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF99FFE3FED8F9E64D04F9B3" bold="true" box="[334,345,1561,1581]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1574">8</emphasis>
) apex of ventral process. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3, 5-7: 0.2 mm; 4, 8: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="0F077D5CFF9EFFE4FF24FE154FCDFDC6" blockId="4.[178,1086,490,600]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="978361D9FF9EFFE4FE97FE154D3FFD9E" box="[257,354,490,512]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="3.[178,218,1516,1536]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1484]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1-8: Stilicoderus rastratus: (1) forebody; (2) median portion of head; (3) sutural portion of elytra; (4) posterior margin of male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6-7) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (8) apex of ventral process. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3, 5-7: 0.2 mm; 4, 8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303006/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">Figs 1, 3</figureCitation>
) approximately as long as pronotum; humeral angles marked; suture somewhat elevated; punctation moderately dense, distinctly coarser than that of head and pronotum; interstices without distinct microsculpture. Hind wings probably present. Metatarsomere I approximately as long as combined length of II and III.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F077D5CFF9EFFE4FF24FD974877FD05" blockId="4.[178,1086,616,667]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">Abdomen approximately as broad as elytra; punctation fine and moderately dense; interstices with shallow microsculpture; posterior margin of tergite VII with palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0F077D5CFF9EFFE4FF51FD544DF5FCA8" blockId="4.[178,1086,682,822]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">
: sternite VII strongly transverse, approximately twice as wide as long, near posterior margin with few modified short and shout setae (
<figureCitation id="978361D9FF9EFFE4FD32FD374EBFFD40" box="[676,738,712,734]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="3.[178,218,1516,1536]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1484]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1-8: Stilicoderus rastratus: (1) forebody; (2) median portion of head; (3) sutural portion of elytra; (4) posterior margin of male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6-7) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (8) apex of ventral process. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3, 5-7: 0.2 mm; 4, 8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303006/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="978361D9FF9EFFE4FC17FD374FE0FD40" box="[897,957,712,734]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="3.[178,218,1516,1536]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1484]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1-8: Stilicoderus rastratus: (1) forebody; (2) median portion of head; (3) sutural portion of elytra; (4) posterior margin of male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6-7) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (8) apex of ventral process. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3, 5-7: 0.2 mm; 4, 8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303006/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) moderately transverse, posterior excision deep and V-shaped, nearly reaching middle of sternite; aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="978361D9FF9EFFE4FEB5FCFD4DDDFC86" box="[291,384,770,792]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="3.[178,218,1516,1536]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,212,1484]" captionTargetId="figure-71@3.[178,1085,212,1497]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs 1-8: Stilicoderus rastratus: (1) forebody; (2) median portion of head; (3) sutural portion of elytra; (4) posterior margin of male sternite VII; (5) male sternite VIII; (6-7) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (8) apex of ventral process. Scale bars: 1: 1.0 mm; 2-3, 5-7: 0.2 mm; 4, 8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303006" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303006/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">Figs 6-8</figureCitation>
) 
<quantity id="C840D0B9FF9EFFE4FE00FCFD4DB7FC86" box="[406,490,770,792]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
long; ventral process slender, straight, and somewhat hatchet-shaped apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="47A22ED7FF9EFFE4FF24FCBA4E74FA38" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0F077D5CFF9EFFE4FF24FCBA4E74FA38" blockId="4.[178,1086,837,1446]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">
Comparative notes: Based on the external and the male sexual characters, 
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FF24FC9C4D74FCE6" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[178,297,867,888]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rastratus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FF24FC9C4D74FCE6" box="[178,297,867,888]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. rastratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
undoubtedly belongs to the 
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FDCEFC9C4E8AFCE6" authorityName="SHIBATA" authorityYear="1968" box="[600,727,867,888]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FDCEFC9C4E8AFCE6" box="[600,727,867,888]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, which previously included two species, the widespread 
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FE41FC7E4EB2FC08" authority="SHIBATA 1968" authorityName="SHIBATA" authorityYear="1968" box="[471,751,896,918]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FE41FC7E4E09FC08" box="[471,596,897,918]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. japonicus</emphasis>
SHIBATA 1968
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FCB4FC7E4CB8FC2D" authority="ROUGEMONT 1996" authorityName="ROUGEMONT" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FCB4FC7E4FEFFC08" box="[802,946,896,918]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. formosanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="6B2900ADFF9EFFE4FC2CFC7E4CB8FC2D" author="ROUGEMONT G" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" pagination="713 - 736" refId="ref7829" refString="ROUGEMONT G. de (1996): Stiliderus and Stilicoderus: New data and new species (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Paederinae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 103 (3): 713 - 736." type="journal article" year="1996">ROUGEMONT 1996</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingCountry id="77AF3DCCFF9EFFE4FF65FC624D1EFC2D" box="[243,323,925,947]" name="Taiwan" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
; 
<collectingCountry id="77AF3DCCFF9EFFE4FED8FC624DD3FC2D" box="[334,398,925,947]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">China</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="CD7CB3BEFF9EFFE4FE0EFC624D83FC2D" box="[408,478,925,947]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">Fujian</collectingRegion>
). It is readily distinguished from the sympatric 
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FC57FC614863FC2D" authorityName="SHIBATA" authorityYear="1968" box="[961,1086,926,947]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FC57FC614863FC2D" box="[961,1086,926,947]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by distinctly smaller size, shorter and less slender antennae (
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FCB2FC444FFCFC4E" authorityName="SHIBATA" authorityYear="1968" box="[804,929,955,976]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FCB2FC444FFCFC4E" box="[804,929,955,976]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: antennomeres II and IV nearly twice as long as broad; preapical antennomeres not distinctly transverse), the relatively larger eyes (
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FD9FFC094ED8FB95" authorityName="SHIBATA" authorityYear="1968" box="[521,645,1014,1035]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FD9FFC094ED8FB95" box="[521,645,1014,1035]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: approximately one fourth as long as postocular region), the much sparser punctation of the head, the less oblong pronotum, the distinctly finer and sparser punctation of the pronotum (
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FD6DFBCE4F24FBD8" authorityName="SHIBATA" authorityYear="1968" box="[763,889,1073,1094]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FD6DFBCE4F24FBD8" box="[763,889,1073,1094]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: punctation dense, rather coarse, and somewhat granulose), the broader impunctate band on the pronotum, and by the male sexual characters (posterior excision of sternite VIII much smaller; aedeagus smaller and with ventral process of different shape). For illustrations of the male sexual characters of 
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FE2DFB594E6AFB25" authorityName="SHIBATA" authorityYear="1968" box="[443,567,1190,1211]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japonicus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FE2DFB594E6AFB25" box="[443,567,1190,1211]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. japonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="6B2900ADFF9EFFE4FDF3FB594F1FFB25" author="ROUGEMONT G" box="[613,834,1189,1211]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" pagination="139 - 187" refId="ref7740" refString="ROUGEMONT G. de (1986 a): Revision of the genus Stiliderus MOTSCHULSKY, 1858, Part I: (= Stilicoderus SHARP, 1889) (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Paederinae). - Entomologische Abhandlungen 49: 139 - 187." type="journal article" year="1986">ROUGEMONT (1986a)</bibRefCitation>
. The new species differs from 
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FF7CFB3C4D27FB46" authorityName="ROUGEMONT" authorityYear="1996" box="[234,378,1218,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FF7CFB3C4D27FB46" box="[234,378,1218,1240]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the more slender body, different head shape (
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FCF9FB3C4FA2FB46" authorityName="ROUGEMONT" authorityYear="1996" box="[879,1023,1218,1240]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FCF9FB3C4FA2FB46" box="[879,1023,1218,1240]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: head nearly subquadrate), the sparser and finer punctation of the head (
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FCC9FB1E4FADFB68" authorityName="ROUGEMONT" authorityYear="1996" box="[863,1008,1248,1270]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FCC9FB1E4FADFB68" box="[863,1008,1248,1270]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: posterior portion of head extensively with dense and rather coarse punctation), the more slender pronotum with much finer and sparser punctation (
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FC90FAE44FC7FAAE" authorityName="ROUGEMONT" authorityYear="1996" box="[774,922,1306,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FC90FAE44FC7FAAE" box="[774,922,1306,1328]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: punctation on either side of the impunctate midline dense and granulose), and the male sexual characters (posterior excision of sternite VIII of different shape; aedeagus smaller and with ventral process of different shape). For illustrations of the male sexual characters of 
<taxonomicName id="C8B806DFFF9EFFE4FBBCFA8C4D75FA38" authorityName="ROUGEMONT" authorityYear="1996" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Stilicoderus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="formosanus">
<emphasis id="3DCCA14EFF9EFFE4FBBCFA8C4D75FA38" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">S. formosanus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="6B2900ADFF9EFFE4FEC3FA6E4E7BFA38" author="ROUGEMONT G" box="[341,550,1424,1446]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" pagination="713 - 736" refId="ref7829" refString="ROUGEMONT G. de (1996): Stiliderus and Stilicoderus: New data and new species (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae, Paederinae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 103 (3): 713 - 736." type="journal article" year="1996">ROUGEMONT (1996)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="47A22ED7FF9EFFE4FF24FA4A4867F998" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0F077D5CFF9EFFE4FF24FA4A4867F998" blockId="4.[178,1086,1461,1542]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">
Distribution and natural history: Thetypelocalityissituatedto the north of Songpan in northern 
<collectingRegion id="CD7CB3BEFF9EFFE4FD9DFA2D4E00FA76" box="[523,605,1490,1512]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation id="978361D9FF9EFFE4FDFDFA2D4EF2FA76" box="[619,687,1490,1512]" captionStart="Map 1" captionStartId="2.[178,223,1012,1032]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,401,994]" captionTargetId="figure-318@2.[178,1085,401,994]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Map 1: Distributions of Stilicoderus japonicus (black circles: examined records; white circles: literature records) and S. rastratus (star)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5303004" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5303004/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575">Map 1</figureCitation>
). The specimens were sifted from leaf litter in a mixed forest with dominant spruce and scattered birch at an altitude of 
<quantity id="C840D0B9FF9EFFE4FC70FA0F486BF998" box="[998,1078,1520,1542]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="1575" unit="m" value="2700.0">2700 m</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
